item.content:encoded: According to an MSNBC poll, "Forty-nine percent of registered voters chose Kerry, compared to 46 percent who re-elected Bush." It'd be interesting if Kerry runs against Bush given that both were in the Skulls & Bones at Yale at the same time (and apparently didn't like each other). There are some who believe that the US Presidents, among other positions of power, are chosen from this secret fraternity.
